<subSubSection id="C30B26F8647DFFE28BAE4D62FC9A145B" pageId="13" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BAE7573647DFFE28BAE4D62FA6D1793" blockId="13.[151,1437,1303,1618]" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B965A961647DFFE28BAE4D62FEF11747" bold="true" box="[151,276,1303,1329]" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
A genus of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C110EF0647DFFE28ACC4D62FD9A1747" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1935" box="[501,639,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pericomaini">Pericomaini</taxonomicName>
, head with eye bridge of 4 facets, distance between eyes 3–4 facet diameters; antenna with scape, pedicel and 14 barrel-shaped flagellomeres; head and thorax without scent or ornamental organs; wing tip between R 
<subScript id="17957736647DFFE28AF64D07FE3217F6" attach="left" box="[463,471,1394,1408]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">4</subScript>
and R 
<subScript id="17957736647DFFE2891B4D04FDCF1709" attach="left" box="[546,554,1393,1407]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">5</subScript>
; terminalia with tubular gonocoxites, gonostyli slightly bent, abruptly thinner in distal half, epandrium rectangular with a pair of pseudospiracular openings, epandrial appendages with two large unequally sized tenacula arranged in line; aedeagus with dorsoventrally flattened ejaculatory apodeme; apical part of ejaculatory apodeme and gonocoxal bridge connected by a V-shaped sclerite with ball-and-socket articulation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE7573647DFFE28BFE4D9AFC5C147F" blockId="13.[151,1437,1303,1618]" box="[199,953,1519,1545]" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">
